            <div id="content-activities" class="tab-content card">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-blue-600 mb-4">Lesson Flow & Activities</h2>
                <p class="text-slate-600 mb-6">The lesson is structured to build conceptual understanding first, using a 5E model. This flow directly targets the identified student needs and misconceptions.</p>
                
                <div class="mb-8">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-800 mb-3">Lesson Sequence</h3>
                    <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:space-x-4 space-y-2 sm:space-y-0 text-center">
                        <div class="flex-1 bg-blue-100 p-3 rounded-lg shadow-sm">
                            <h4 class="font-semibold text-blue-800">1. Engage</h4>
                            <p class="text-sm text-blue-700">"Is This Work?" Hook (Confronts misconception)</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="flex-shrink-0 sm:self-center text-slate-500 font-bold">&#10140;</div>
                        <div class="flex-1 bg-blue-100 p-3 rounded-lg shadow-sm">
                            <h4 class="font-semibold text-blue-800">2. Explore & Explain</h4>
                            <p class="text-sm text-blue-700">Defining the "Two Conditions" for Work</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="flex-shrink-0 sm:self-center text-slate-500 font-bold">&#10140;</div>
                        <div class="flex-1 bg-blue-100 p-3 rounded-lg shadow-sm">
                            <h4 class="font-semibold text-blue-800">3. Elaborate</h4>
                            <p class="text-sm text-blue-700">Whiteboard "Work or No Work?" Activity</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="flex-shrink-0 sm:self-center text-slate-500 font-bold">&#10140;</div>
                        <div class="flex-1 bg-blue-100 p-3 rounded-lg shadow-sm">
                            <h4 class="font-semibold text-blue-800">4. Evaluate</h4>
                            <p class="text-sm text-blue-700">Choice Board & Exit Ticket</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-800 mb-3">Differentiated for All Learners</h3>
                    <p class="text-slate-600 mb-4">The plan is "built for the edges" to challenge and support every student.</p>
                    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
                        <div class="bg-slate-50 p-4 rounded-lg border border-slate-200">
                            <h4 class="font-semibold text-slate-700">For Conceptual Learners</h4>
                            <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Use concrete demos (pushing wall, holding books) to make the abstract visible.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="bg-slate-50 p-4 rounded-lg border border-slate-200">
                            <h4 class="font-semibold text-slate-700">For Algebra-Strong Students</h4>
                            <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Challenge with conceptual "traps" like the 'Waiter Challenge' problem.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="bg-slate-50 p-4 rounded-lg border border-slate-200">
                            <h4 class="font-semibold text-slate-700">For Students Needing Support</h4>
                            <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Provide a "Two-Condition Checklist" (Force? Yes/No. Movement? Yes/No).</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="bg-slate-50 p-4 rounded-lg border border-slate-200">
                            <h4 class="font-semibold text-slate-700">For Advanced Students</h4>
                            <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Push with "What if..." extension questions (e.g., 'What if the waiter lifts the tray?').</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div id="content-assessment" class="tab-content">
                <p class="text-slate-600 mb-6 text-center text-lg">Assessment is continuous and varied, focusing on both self-reflection and peer-to-peer discussion to correct misconceptions as they happen.</p>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                    <div class="card">
                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-blue-600 mb-4">Checks for Understanding</h2>
                        <div class="space-y-4">
                            <div>
                                <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-800">Live Formative Assessment</h3>
                                <p class="text-slate-600">The "Work or No Work?" whiteboard activity is the key assessment.</p>
                                <p class="mt-2 text-sm bg-blue-50 text-blue-800 p-3 rounded-lg">
                                    <strong>Rationale (Accomplished):</strong> This allows for **real-time student self-evaluation** and provides data for **immediate, individualized teacher feedback**.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <div>
                                <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-800">Peer Assessment</h3>
                                <p class="text-slate-600">"Think-Pair-Share" during the "Engage" activity encourages students to defend their reasoning to each other.</p>
                            </div>
                            <div>
                                <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-800">Summative Assessment</h3>
                                <p class="text-slate-600">The "Intro to Work & Energy Choice Board" and a final exit ticket measure individual mastery of the objectives.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card">
                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-blue-600 mb-4">Anticipated Obstacle</h2>
                        <p class="text-slate-600 mb-4">The primary obstacle is the conflict between the "everyday" and "physics" definitions of work.</p>
                        <div class="bg-red-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
                            <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-900">Misconception</h4>
                            <p class="text-red-800">"I'm working hard just by holding these heavy books!"</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="text-center my-4">
                            <span class="text-2xl text-slate-400">&#11015;</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="bg-green-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
                            <h4 class="font-semibold text-green-900">Solution</h4>
                            <p class="text-green-800">The lesson will **acknowledge** "muscle work" (biological effort) while explicitly differentiating it from "physics work" (work done *on the object*), which requires displacement.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div id="content-professionalism" class="tab-content card">
